# Large data directories
# NOTE: `data/` and `indices/` are no longer blanket-ignored. The
# 2026-04-14 v3 sprint audit found that `data/augmentation/*.py` and
# `data/preprocessing/*.py` — ~3000 lines of Python source used by
# Task 2, Task 3, and the existing preprocessing pipeline — had
# been silently excluded from git history since project inception
# because of the blanket `data/` rule. Actual binary / large data
# artifacts are already caught by the file-extension patterns above
# (*.csv, *.json, *.npy, *.pt, *.pth, *.bin, *.safetensors, *.pkl,
# *.png, *.jpg, *.dcm, *.ipynb) so removing the directory rules is
# safe and lets Python source under these paths flow into git.
checkpoints/
